      • testCalcAverage

        public void testCalcAverage()
        Test method for Student.calcAverage(). This test is very long, because we had to build a hole structure of students that have answered questions, in units, in courses. This test is very long, because we had to build a hole structure of students that have answered questions, in units, in courses. The student s1 will be a student that applies and is accepted to the courses c1 and c2. These courses will have 2 exercises each and s1 will answer to the four of them, in some exercises he will get the highest mark and will get more average marks in the others. The student s2 will apply for courses c1 and c2, but will only be accepted in c1. He will leave questions unanswered and get the lowest possible mark (meaning that he will have a negative mark because of the penalty, resulting in a 0 in the exercise mark because no negative marks are allowed) The student s3 will apply for course c1 and c2, and will be accepted in both, but will not do any exercise. The student s4 will not apply to any course. The averages of each student have been approximated. That is why we won't usually be comparing them with "==", but with a upper bound and a lower bound to our approximations, using the operators "<" and ">".
